.TH TREAD 1 "March 2026" "tread 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tread \- terminal EPUB reader
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tread
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIfile.epub\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tread
is a terminal-based EPUB reader with support for text formatting, link
following, table of contents navigation, theme customization, and reading
position persistence.
.PP
It supports both EPUB 2 and EPUB 3 formats and renders XHTML content with
bold, italic, underline, and heading formatting using ncurses.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-vi
Use vi-style keybindings instead of the default nano-style bindings.
.TP
.BI \-\-theme " NAME"
Use the named color theme. Available themes can be browsed using the
in-application theme selector.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-restore
Don't restore the previous reading position. Start from the beginning
of the book.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display usage information and exit.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Display version information and exit.
.SH NANO-STYLE KEYBINDINGS (DEFAULT)
.TP
.B Arrow Down/Up
Scroll down/up one line.
.TP
.B PgDn, Space
Scroll down one page.
.TP
.B PgUp, Backspace
Scroll up one page.
.TP
.B Ctrl+N
Next chapter.
.TP
.B Ctrl+P
Previous chapter.
.TP
.B Ctrl+T
Open table of contents.
.TP
.B Ctrl+W
Search.
.TP
.B Tab / Shift+Tab
Cycle forward/backward through links.
.TP
.B Enter
Follow selected link, or scroll down if no link is selected.
.TP
.B Ctrl+B
Go back (after following a link).
.TP
.B Ctrl+E
Open theme selector.
.TP
.B Ctrl+G
Show help.
.TP
.B Ctrl+X
Quit.
.SH VI-STYLE KEYBINDINGS
.TP
.B j/k, Arrow Down/Up
Scroll down/up one line.
.TP
.B Ctrl+F, Space, PgDn
Scroll down one page.
.TP
.B Ctrl+B, PgUp
Scroll up one page.
.TP
.B Ctrl+D / Ctrl+U
Scroll down/up half a page.
.TP
.B l/h, ]/[
Next/previous chapter.
.TP
.B t
Open table of contents.
.TP
.B /
Search forward.
.TP
.B ?
Search backward.
.TP
.B n / N
Next/previous search match.
.TP
.B Tab / Shift+Tab
Cycle forward/backward through links.
.TP
.B Enter
Follow selected link.
.TP
.B Backspace
Go back.
.TP
.B T
Open theme selector.
.TP
.B q
Quit.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration is read from
.IR ~/.config/tread/tread.conf .
.PP
Example configuration:
.PP
.nf
.RS
# Keybinding mode: nano (default) or vi
mode = vi

# Default theme name
theme = dark
.RE
.fi
.SH THEMES
Themes are stored as INI files in
.IR ~/.config/tread/themes/*.conf .
.PP
Colors are ncurses color numbers (0\-7 for basic colors, 0\-255 for extended),
or \fB\-1\fR / \fBdefault\fR for the terminal default color.
.PP
Example theme file:
.PP
.nf
.RS
name = solarized
fg = 12
bg = 8
status_fg = 0
status_bg = 3
link_fg = 4
link_bg = -1
heading_fg = 3
heading_bg = -1
.RE
.fi
.PP
Three built-in themes are included: \fBdefault\fR, \fBdark\fR, and \fBlight\fR.
.SH STATE PERSISTENCE
Reading position is automatically saved on exit and restored when reopening
the same file. State files are stored in
.IR ~/.local/share/tread/state/ .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/tread/tread.conf
Main configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.config/tread/themes/*.conf
Custom theme files.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/tread/state/
Saved reading positions.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful execution.
.TP
.B 1
Error (invalid arguments, cannot open file, etc).
